</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-122_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Quantifying the impact of distributed intelligence can be tricky as its benefits are often indirect and long-term. However, businesses can look at metrics like the number of new ideas generated, the speed of problem resolution, or improvements in product innovation to gauge its effectiveness.
